      &lt;dd&gt;
        &lt;ul&gt;
          
          &lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;=0.2.0&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
          
        &lt;/ul&gt;
      &lt;/dd&gt;
      
      &lt;dt&gt;&lt;code&gt;hivex::Hive::from_handle&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;
      &lt;dd&gt;
        &lt;ul&gt;
          
          &lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;=0.2.0&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
          
        &lt;/ul&gt;
      &lt;/dd&gt;
      
    &lt;/dl&gt;
    

    

    &lt;h3 id=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Description&lt;/h3&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;Drop&lt;/code&gt; implementation for &lt;code&gt;Hive&lt;/code&gt; did perform free, but so did &lt;code&gt;Hive::close&lt;/code&gt;, which,
at the end of the scope performed &lt;code&gt;Drop&lt;/code&gt;, therefore triggering double-free.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additionally, function &lt;code&gt;Hive::from_handle&lt;/code&gt; was not marked as unsafe, making it,
in combination with &lt;code&gt;as_handle&lt;/code&gt; easy to clone and trigger double-free in safe
code or triggering UB when using invalid pointer.&lt;/p&gt;


